### HTML5 Basics Cheatsheet ###

Doc: https://www.w3schools.com/tags/

## head meta tags ##
<!DOCTYPE html >
<!DOCTYPE html lang="de-CH"> (Read more about Language & Country Codes)
<title>Title<title>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="author" content="name">
<meta name="description" content="description">
<meta name="keywords" content="keywords">
<meta name="robots" content="index,follow">
<meta name="date" content="2010-05-15T08:49:37+02:00">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, user-scalable=yes">
<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="30">
<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">

## head links tags ##
<link href="css/style.css" rel="stylesheet">
<link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="favicon.png">
<link rel="canonical" href="https://example.com/content.html">
<script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js">
<script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js">

## Section tags ##
<header>		header section
<nav>			navigation section
<main>			main content area
<section>		additional sections
<article>		content like blog post
<aside>			area aside from the content
<address>		adress element
<footer>		footer section

## Media tags ##
<canvas>		area to draw via js
<svg>			area to draw via svg
<audio>			sound content
<video>			video content
<source>		specify media ressources
<embed>			container for a plugin
<track>			specify text in media-tag

## Lists ##
ul				Unordered list
ol				Ordered list
li				List item
dl				description list
dt				description term
dd				description data
display:inline	CSS property to display a list horizontally

## Tables ##
tr				Row
th				Header Cell
td				Cell
caption			Caption
colgroup		groupes one or more columns
col				Properties for each column in a colgroup
thead			Groupes the header content
tbody			Groupes the body content
tfoot			Groupes the footer content

	<table style="width:100%">
	  <tr>
	    <th>Firstname</th>
	    <th>Lastname</th>
	    <th>Age</th>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
	    <td>Jill</td>
	    <td>Smith</td>
	    <td>50</td>
	  </tr>
	  <tr>
	    <td>Eve</td>
	    <td>Jackson</td>
	    <td>94</td>
	  </tr>
	 </table>

